http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/100-kg-of-ganja-seized-in-raid/article14017331.ece

A day after the police seized 300 kg ganja from an abandoned lorry in the outskirts of the city, the cops on Saturday conducted raid on a house at Bharati Nagar and seized 100 kg of the contraband.The Ibrahimpatnam police, who seized the hemp on Friday, took a few suspects into custody. Based on their confession, the police confiscated the contraband on the second day on Saturday. Police are now probing on the activities of ganja smuggling rackets, which were being operated from the neighbouring States and the Agency areas in Andhra Pradesh.